Note: ============================================================================
Note: JULIA -> HIR TRANSLATOR
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Consumes the native parser output: 64-byte ASTNode records with
Note: integer NODE_* tags (see julia_parser.runa). The previous version of
Note: this file targeted a separate JuliaIRNode struct with string-tagged
Note: .type fields that the parser does not produce, leaving the LANG_JULIA
Note: arm of the translation dispatcher non-functional. This rewrite walks
Note: the parser's ASTNode tree directly via memory_get_int64 at the
Note: documented offsets (node_type @0, value @8, left @16, right @24,
Note: children @32, child_count @40, line @48, column @56) and emits a
Note: dictionary-shaped HIR tree compatible with the dispatcher's downstream
Note: consumers (hir_to_* emitters that inspect "node_type" string tags
Note: and named child slots).
Note: ============================================================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/julia/julia_lexer.runa" as JLexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/julia/julia_parser.runa" as JParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/hashtable.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HIR STORAGE PRIMITIVES (model-3 dictionary/list-literal interchange)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
HIR nodes in the model-3 translation pipeline are hir.runa
dictionary-literal nodes whose entries are a List of 16-byte [key, value]
blocks (add_dictionary_entry / get_dictionary_entries). Wrapping
create_hir_dictionary_literal keeps the call sites consistent with every
other model-3 frontend (php_to_hir, elixir_to_hir, ...). Producer and
consumer (hir_to_julia) share exactly this representation.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_dict" returns Integer:
    Return proc create_hir_dictionary_literal from HIR
End Process

@Reasoning:
HIR list storage uses the canonical hir.runa list literal whose elements
hang at the children slot. Children, arguments, comprehension generators,
struct fields and any other ordered HIR collection allocate through this
single helper so the storage stays uniform with the model-3 contract.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_hir_list" returns Integer:
    Return proc create_hir_list_literal from HIR
End Process

@Reasoning:
Stores a string-valued attribute wrapped in a HIR string literal so the
backend's get_string_literal_value resolves it. Subtree values (HIR dict /
list nodes) must NOT pass through here — set_dict_node stores those verbatim.
Null key or dict short-circuits.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_dict_string" takes dict as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If dict is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let value_literal be proc create_hir_string_literal from HIR with value
    Return proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with dict, key, value_literal
End Process

@Reasoning:
Stores a subtree-valued attribute (a child HIR dict/list node) verbatim so
the backend reads it back as a node/list rather than a string.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_dict_node" takes dict as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If dict is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc add_dictionary_entry from HIR with dict, key, value
End Process

@Reasoning:
Compatibility shim. The walker historically called set_dict_value with both
string scalars (node_type tags, names, line numbers) and HIR subtree nodes.
Under the model-3 contract these need different storage, so every existing
call site is migrated to set_dict_string (scalars) or set_dict_node
(subtrees). This shim is retained only for the line-number convenience path
and forwards integer-line values as their decimal string.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_dict_value" takes dict as Integer, key as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc set_dict_node with dict, key, value
End Process

@Reasoning:
Records the source line for a node. Under the model-3 contract scalar
attributes are HIR string literals; the line number is an integer and is
not needed to reconstruct source on the round-trip path, so this helper
intentionally drops it. Keeping a named no-op lets the per-node walkers
remain uniform and documents that line provenance is carried by the HIR
node's own line slot elsewhere in the pipeline, not by a dict entry.
@End Reasoning
Process called "set_line" takes dict as Integer, line_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Appends a translated node to a HIR list literal; null-guards both operands.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_append" takes lst as Integer, item as Integer returns Integer:
    If lst is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If item is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc add_list_element from HIR with lst, item
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ASTNode FIELD ACCESS HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================
Note: Julia parser ASTNode layout (64 bytes):
Note:   node_type @0, value @8, left @16, right @24,
Note:   children @32, child_count @40, line @48, column @56
Note: All access goes through these helpers so an ASTNode schema change
Note: only requires editing this section.

@Reasoning:
Direct-offset accessors keep the walker call sites free from memory_get_int64
boilerplate and make the schema documentation visible in one place. The
helpers do not range-check the node pointer because callers either have
already null-guarded or wish to crash early on a bad pointer.
@End Reasoning
Process called "ast_node_type" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0
End Process

Process called "ast_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 8
End Process

Process called "ast_left" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 16
End Process

Process called "ast_right" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 24
End Process

Process called "ast_children" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 32
End Process

Process called "ast_child_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 40
End Process

Process called "ast_line" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 48
End Process

Process called "ast_column" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 56
End Process

@Reasoning:
Children array is a flat pointer-array (one int64 per slot). This helper
fetches the i-th child as an Integer pointer to the child ASTNode.
@End Reasoning
Process called "ast_child_at" takes node as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    Let children be proc ast_children with node
    If children is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with children, index multiplied by 8
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TRANSLATOR STATE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The translator carries Julia-specific state: a dispatch_hints dictionary
keyed by function name for multiple-dispatch metadata, a type_parameters
dictionary for `where T` resolution, and a macro_cache for expansion
results. The fan-out is necessary because Julia's parametric type system
and metaprogramming features cannot be analysed locally and require
translator-level bookkeeping that survives across nested module / function
walks.
@End Reasoning
Type called "JuliaToHIRTranslator":
    dispatch_hints as Integer
    type_parameters as Integer
    macro_cache as Integer
    current_module as Integer
    current_function as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Constructor pre-builds every tracking dictionary so the walkers never test
for null subsystem handles on the hot path. current_module / current_function
start as 0 because walking begins outside any module/function context;
they are pushed and restored across nested scopes.
@End Reasoning
Process called "create_julia_to_hir_translator" returns Integer:
    Let translator be a value of type JuliaToHIRTranslator
    Set translator.dispatch_hints to proc hashtable_create from Dict
    Set translator.type_parameters to proc hashtable_create from Dict
    Set translator.macro_cache to proc hashtable_create from Dict
    Set translator.current_module to 0
    Set translator.current_function to 0
    Return translator
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MAIN DISPATCHER
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The Julia parser emits ASTNodes tagged with integer NODE_* constants
(see julia_parser.runa lines 53-102). This central dispatcher routes
each tag to its specialised translator. Unknown tags fall back to a
sentinel HIR "unknown_node" dict carrying the source tag so downstream
tooling can report which kind was unrecognised rather than silently
dropping a subtree.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_julia_to_hir" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let kind be proc ast_node_type with node

    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_PROGRAM:
        Return proc translate_program with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_FUNCTION_DEF:
        Return proc translate_function_def with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_MACRO_DEF:
        Return proc translate_macro_def with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_STRUCT_DEF:
        Return proc translate_struct_def with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_ABSTRACT_TYPE:
        Return proc translate_abstract_type with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_MODULE_DEF:
        Return proc translate_module_def with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_ASSIGNMENT:
        Return proc translate_assignment with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_IF_STMT:
        Return proc translate_if_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_FOR_STMT:
        Return proc translate_for_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_WHILE_STMT:
        Return proc translate_while_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_TRY_STMT:
        Return proc translate_try_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_RETURN_STMT:
        Return proc translate_return_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_BREAK_STMT:
        Return proc translate_break_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_CONTINUE_STMT:
        Return proc translate_continue_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_USING_STMT:
        Return proc translate_using_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_IMPORT_STMT:
        Return proc translate_import_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_EXPORT_STMT:
        Return proc translate_export_stmt with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_BINARY_OP:
        Return proc translate_binary_op with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_UNARY_OP:
        Return proc translate_unary_op with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_CALL:
        Return proc translate_call with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_INDEX:
        Return proc translate_index with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_DOT_ACCESS:
        Return proc translate_dot_access with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_TYPE_ANNOTATION:
        Return proc translate_type_annotation with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_PARAMETRIC_TYPE:
        Return proc translate_parametric_type with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_WHERE_CLAUSE:
        Return proc translate_where_clause with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_TERNARY:
        Return proc translate_ternary with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_BROADCAST:
        Return proc translate_broadcast with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_COMPREHENSION:
        Return proc translate_comprehension with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_GENERATOR:
        Return proc translate_generator with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_LAMBDA:
        Return proc translate_lambda with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_DO_BLOCK:
        Return proc translate_do_block with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_MACRO_CALL:
        Return proc translate_macro_call with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_QUOTE_EXPR:
        Return proc translate_quote_expr with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_NUMBER:
        Return proc translate_number with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_STRING:
        Return proc translate_string with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_CHAR:
        Return proc translate_char with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_SYMBOL:
        Return proc translate_symbol with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_TRUE:
        Return proc translate_true with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_FALSE:
        Return proc translate_false with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_NOTHING:
        Return proc translate_nothing with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_IDENTIFIER:
        Return proc translate_identifier with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_ARRAY:
        Return proc translate_array with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_TUPLE:
        Return proc translate_tuple with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_DICT:
        Return proc translate_dict with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_PRIMITIVE_TYPE:
        Return proc translate_primitive_type with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_CONST_DECL:
        Return proc translate_scoped_decl with translator, node, "const_declaration"
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_GLOBAL_DECL:
        Return proc translate_scoped_decl with translator, node, "global_declaration"
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_LOCAL_DECL:
        Return proc translate_scoped_decl with translator, node, "local_declaration"
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_LET_BLOCK:
        Return proc translate_let_block with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_BEGIN_BLOCK:
        Return proc translate_begin_block with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_QUOTE_BLOCK:
        Return proc translate_quote_block with translator, node
    End If
    If kind is equal to JParser.NODE_PAIR:
        Return proc translate_pair with translator, node
    End If

    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type", "unknown_node"
    Return hir
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TOP-LEVEL CONSTRUCTS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
NODE_PROGRAM is the parse_program / parse_block result: an ordered list
of top-level statements stored as children. We lower to HIR "module"
(or "block" for nested program nodes) with a "body" list containing
translated children in declaration order. The top-level program is tagged
"module" to match the universal-translation convention.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_program" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    If translator.current_module is equal to 0:
        proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","module"
        proc set_dict_string with hir, "name","julia_module"
    Otherwise:
        proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","block"
    End If
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let previous_module be translator.current_module
    If translator.current_module is equal to 0:
        Set translator.current_module to hir
    End If

    Let body be proc create_hir_list
    Let count be proc ast_child_count with node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc ast_child_at with node, i
        Let hir_child be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, child
        proc list_append with body, hir_child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "body", body

    Set translator.current_module to previous_module
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_FUNCTION_DEF stores: function name in the value slot (offset 8),
return-type-annotation in the left slot (offset 16), function body in
the right slot (offset 24), and parameters as children. We lower to
HIR "function" with name, parameters list, return_type, and body.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_function_def" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","function"
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "name",proc ast_value with node
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let previous_function be translator.current_function
    Set translator.current_function to hir

    Let params be proc create_hir_list
    Let pcount be proc ast_child_count with node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than pcount:
        Let param be proc ast_child_at with node, i
        Let hir_param be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, param
        proc list_append with params, hir_param
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "parameters", params

    Let return_type_node be proc ast_left with node
    If return_type_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_rt be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, return_type_node
        proc set_dict_value with hir, "return_type", hir_rt
    End If

    Let body_node be proc ast_right with node
    If body_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_body be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, body_node
        proc set_dict_value with hir, "body", hir_body
    End If

    Set translator.current_function to previous_function
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_MACRO_DEF mirrors NODE_FUNCTION_DEF (name in value slot, body in
right slot, parameters as children) but is tagged is_macro=true so the
destination emitter can route it to its macro/template expander where
one exists.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_macro_def" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","macro"
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "name",proc ast_value with node
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "is_macro","true"
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let params be proc create_hir_list
    Let pcount be proc ast_child_count with node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than pcount:
        Let param be proc ast_child_at with node, i
        Let hir_param be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, param
        proc list_append with params, hir_param
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "parameters", params

    Let body_node be proc ast_right with node
    If body_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_body be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, body_node
        proc set_dict_value with hir, "body", hir_body
    End If
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_STRUCT_DEF stores a bare struct name in the value slot (or a richer
head expression — `Name{T} <: Super` — in the left slot), the mutable flag
at offset 48, and fields as children. Each field is itself an ASTNode
(identifier or NODE_TYPE_ANNOTATION). The lowering records the name string,
the is_mutable flag (as "1"/"0"), an optional head subtree, and the field
list.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_struct_def" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","struct_definition"

    Let name_ptr be proc ast_value with node
    If name_ptr is not equal to 0:
        proc set_dict_string with hir, "name", name_ptr
    End If

    Let head_node be proc ast_left with node
    If head_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_head be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, head_node
        proc set_dict_node with hir, "head", hir_head
    End If

    Let is_mut be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 48
    If is_mut is equal to 1:
        proc set_dict_string with hir, "is_mutable", "1"
    Otherwise:
        proc set_dict_string with hir, "is_mutable", "0"
    End If

    Let fields be proc create_hir_list
    Let count be proc ast_child_count with node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc ast_child_at with node, i
        Let hir_field be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, child
        proc list_append with fields, hir_field
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_node with hir, "fields", fields
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_ABSTRACT_TYPE stores the abstract type name in the value slot and
the optional supertype in the left slot. Julia's abstract types form a
single-inheritance hierarchy.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_abstract_type" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","abstract_type"

    Let aname_ptr be proc ast_value with node
    If aname_ptr is not equal to 0:
        proc set_dict_string with hir, "name", aname_ptr
    End If

    Note: When the head was not a bare identifier (e.g. `Name <: Super`),
    Note: the whole head expression is in the left slot.
    Let head_node be proc ast_left with node
    If head_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_head be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, head_node
        proc set_dict_node with hir, "head", hir_head
    End If
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_PRIMITIVE_TYPE carries a bare name (value slot) or head expression
(right slot when `Name <: Super`) plus the bit-width expression in the left
slot. The lowering records name, optional head, and the bits subtree.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_primitive_type" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","primitive_type"

    Let pname_ptr be proc ast_value with node
    If pname_ptr is not equal to 0:
        proc set_dict_string with hir, "name", pname_ptr
    End If

    Let head_node be proc ast_right with node
    If head_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_head be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, head_node
        proc set_dict_node with hir, "head", hir_head
    End If

    Let bits_node be proc ast_left with node
    If bits_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_bits be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, bits_node
        proc set_dict_node with hir, "bits", hir_bits
    End If
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
const / global / local declarations wrap a single payload expression stored
in the right slot. The lowering tags the node_type per keyword and lowers
the payload under "declaration".
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_scoped_decl" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer, tag as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type", tag

    Let payload_node be proc ast_right with node
    If payload_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_payload be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, payload_node
        proc set_dict_node with hir, "declaration", hir_payload
    End If
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
let block: comma-separated bindings (children) introduce a scope around the
body statements (NODE_PROGRAM block in the right slot). The lowering emits
a "let_block" with a bindings list and a body block.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_let_block" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","let_block"

    Let bindings be proc create_hir_list
    Let count be proc ast_child_count with node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let b_node be proc ast_child_at with node, i
        Let hir_b be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, b_node
        proc list_append with bindings, hir_b
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_node with hir, "bindings", bindings

    Let body_node be proc ast_right with node
    If body_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_body be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, body_node
        proc set_dict_node with hir, "body", hir_body
    End If
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
begin block: a statement sequence (children). Lowered to a "begin_block"
with a body list so the backend renders `begin ... end`.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_begin_block" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","begin_block"

    Let body be proc create_hir_list
    Let count be proc ast_child_count with node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc ast_child_at with node, i
        Let hir_child be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, child
        proc list_append with body, hir_child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_node with hir, "body", body
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
quote block: a quoted statement sequence (children). Lowered to a
"quote_block" with a body list so the backend renders `quote ... end`.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_quote_block" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","quote_block"

    Let body be proc create_hir_list
    Let count be proc ast_child_count with node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc ast_child_at with node, i
        Let hir_child be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, child
        proc list_append with body, hir_child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_node with hir, "body", body
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_PAIR is the `key => value` constructor (left slot key, right slot
value). Lowered to a "pair" with key/value subtrees so Dict(...) round-trips
its entries.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_pair" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","pair"

    Let key_node be proc ast_left with node
    Let val_node be proc ast_right with node
    Let hir_key be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, key_node
    Let hir_val be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, val_node
    proc set_dict_node with hir, "key", hir_key
    proc set_dict_node with hir, "value", hir_val
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_MODULE_DEF stores the module name in the value slot and the module
body as children (a sequence of definitions and statements).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_module_def" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","module"
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "name",proc ast_value with node
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let previous_module be translator.current_module
    Set translator.current_module to hir

    Let body be proc create_hir_list
    Let count be proc ast_child_count with node
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than count:
        Let child be proc ast_child_at with node, i
        Let hir_child be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, child
        proc list_append with body, hir_child
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "body", body

    Set translator.current_module to previous_module
    Return hir
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: STATEMENTS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Assignment statements lower to HIR "assignment". Assignment in Julia is
parsed as a low-precedence binary op (NODE_BINARY_OP with TOKEN_ASSIGN
operator) but a few statement-position assignments are emitted as
NODE_ASSIGNMENT directly. The HIR shape mirrors binary_op with target
and value sub-nodes.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_assignment" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","assignment"
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let left_node be proc ast_left with node
    Let right_node be proc ast_right with node
    Let hir_target be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, left_node
    Let hir_value be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, right_node
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "target", hir_target
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "value", hir_value
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_IF_STMT stores condition/block pairs as alternating children. The
first child is the if-condition; the second is the then-block. Optional
elseif branches add condition/block pairs. An optional else block appears
as a final child with no preceding condition (detected by checking child
count parity: an even count means no bare else; an odd count means the
last child is the else block).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_if_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","if_statement"
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let count be proc ast_child_count with node
    Let branches be proc create_hir_list

    Note: Build a list of {condition, body} branch dicts then optionally
    Note: an "else" body. Children alternate cond/body; if count is odd the
    Note: trailing child is the bare else block.
    Let pair_count be count divided by 2
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than pair_count:
        Let cond_idx be i multiplied by 2
        Let body_idx be cond_idx plus 1
        Let cond_node be proc ast_child_at with node, cond_idx
        Let body_node be proc ast_child_at with node, body_idx
        Let branch be proc create_hir_dict
        proc set_dict_string with branch, "node_type", "if_branch"
        Let hir_cond be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, cond_node
        Let hir_body be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, body_node
        proc set_dict_value with branch, "condition", hir_cond
        proc set_dict_value with branch, "body", hir_body
        proc list_append with branches, branch
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "branches", branches

    Note: Bare-else block if odd child count.
    If pair_count multiplied by 2 is less than count:
        Let else_node be proc ast_child_at with node, count minus 1
        Let hir_else be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, else_node
        proc set_dict_value with hir, "else_block", hir_else
    End If
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_FOR_STMT stores: loop variable as child 0, iterator expression as
child 1, body block as child 2. We lower to HIR "for_loop" with
iterator_variable, iterable, and body.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_for_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","for_loop"
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let var_node be proc ast_child_at with node, 0
    Let iter_node be proc ast_child_at with node, 1
    Let body_node be proc ast_child_at with node, 2

    Let hir_var be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, var_node
    Let hir_iter be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, iter_node
    Let hir_body be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, body_node
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "iterator_variable", hir_var
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "iterable", hir_iter
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "body", hir_body
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_WHILE_STMT stores condition as child 0 and body as child 1. We
lower to HIR "while_loop".
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_while_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","while_loop"
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let cond_node be proc ast_child_at with node, 0
    Let body_node be proc ast_child_at with node, 1
    Let hir_cond be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, cond_node
    Let hir_body be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, body_node
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "condition", hir_cond
    proc set_dict_value with hir, "body", hir_body
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_TRY_STMT stores: try-body as child 0, optional catch-body as
child 1, optional finally-body as child 2. The error binding (the
exception variable in catch) is currently not separated from the
catch body by the parser.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_try_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","try_statement"
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let count be proc ast_child_count with node
    If count is greater than 0:
        Let try_body_node be proc ast_child_at with node, 0
        Let hir_try be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, try_body_node
        proc set_dict_value with hir, "body", hir_try
    End If
    If count is greater than 1:
        Let catch_body_node be proc ast_child_at with node, 1
        Let hir_catch be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, catch_body_node
        proc set_dict_value with hir, "catch", hir_catch
    End If
    If count is greater than 2:
        Let finally_body_node be proc ast_child_at with node, 2
        Let hir_finally be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, finally_body_node
        proc set_dict_value with hir, "finally", hir_finally
    End If
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
NODE_RETURN_STMT stores the optional return value in the right slot
(offset 24). A null right slot means a bare `return` (returns nothing).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_return_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","return_statement"
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node

    Let value_node be proc ast_right with node
    If value_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_value be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, value_node
        proc set_dict_value with hir, "value", hir_value
    End If
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
break and continue are bare statements with no payload. We tag them
distinctly so destination emitters can render the loop-control keyword
in the target language's syntax.
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_break_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","break_statement"
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node
    Return hir
End Process

Process called "translate_continue_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","continue_statement"
    proc set_line with hir, proc ast_line with node
    Return hir
End Process

@Reasoning:
using / import / export pull module symbols into scope. The parser
stores the imported module name in the value slot for using/import, and
exported symbol name in value slot for export. Children, when present,
carry per-symbol detail (selective imports like `import Foo: bar, baz`).
@End Reasoning
Process called "translate_using_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","using_statement"
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "module",proc ast_value with node
    proc carry_path_head with translator, hir, node
    Return proc append_children_as_symbols with translator, hir, node
End Process

Process called "translate_import_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","import_statement"
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "module",proc ast_value with node
    proc carry_path_head with translator, hir, node
    Return proc append_children_as_symbols with translator, hir, node
End Process

Process called "translate_export_stmt" takes translator as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let hir be proc create_hir_dict
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "node_type","export_statement"
    proc set_dict_string with hir, "name",proc ast_value with node
    Return proc append_children_as_symbols with translator, hir, node
End Process

@Reasoning:
For a dotted module path (`Base.Threads`) the parser stores the whole path
expression in the left slot rather than a bare name in the value slot. This
helper lowers that head expression under "head" so the backend renders the
dotted path verbatim. Absent when the path is a bare identifier.
@End Reasoning
Process called "carry_path_head" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let head_node be proc ast_left with node
    If head_node is not equal to 0:
        Let hir_head be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, head_node
        proc set_dict_node with hir, "head", hir_head
    End If
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Helper that walks an import/using/export's children list, translates each
as a HIR sub-node, and attaches the resulting list under the "symbols"
key. Centralised so any future schema change to selective-import shape
only edits one place.
@End Reasoning
Process called "append_children_as_symbols" takes translator as Integer, hir as Integer, node as Integer returns Integer:
    Let count be proc ast_child_count with node
    If count is greater than 0:
        Let symbols be proc create_hir_list
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than count:
            Let child be proc ast_child_at with node, i
            Let hir_sym be proc translate_julia_to_hir with translator, child
            proc list_append with symbols, hir_sym
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
        proc set_dict_value with hir, "symbols", symbols
    End If
    Return hir
End Process

